name: Trinity Health Urgent Care
directions: Located next to receptionists desk in waiting lounge.
comment:
Waiting lounge for this urgent care center has one unisex bathroom. 

Doctors are friendly and appear trans-accepting, as they ask questions such as “preferred pronouns and name?”

name: Dockers
directions: Gendered single stall bathrooms located in outside venue, which can be accessed through the indoor venue.
comment:
This is a restaurant that does require you to be a paying customer to use the bathrooms. There are single stall gendered bathrooms located in the outside venue. There are also multi-stalled gendered bathrooms inside the restaurant. 

It does not inherently promote itself as a safe space.

name: Explorer’s Learning Center
directions:
Multiple bathrooms in every center. In classrooms, bathrooms are exclusively for teachers, students, approved visitors, etc. 

However, the office located in the white building has a unisex bathroom that is available to others. It’s located past the office, toward the finger printing station in the back.
comment: A very open-minded, inclusive, and welcoming center. The center itself openly and frequently supports lgbt+ rights. It promotes itself as a safe space.

name: Sei Bella Tattoo Parlor
directions: Located in the back of the shop past the tattoo rooms
comment: Very open-minded, inclusive, and welcoming tattoo parlor run by all women tattoo artists. There’s only one bathroom available in the parlor, but its unisex.

name: Game Kastle
directions: Back room to right
comment: Single occupancy gender neutral that is about 10x10ft. The store allows free use of the game area for borrowing or playing board games, so people regularly use the restroom without paying.

name: BLKdog Coffee
directions: Customers only, go all the way to the back past the counter.
comment: Men's room is a onesie with a urinal and toilet! Wish they made more for STP practice.

name: 411 South Bar & Grill

comment: Apologies that I don’t remember the accessibility or changing tables scenario, but I remember them being gendered single stall

name: Monster Monkey Studios Custom Tattoos

comment: This is a safe space for LGBTQIA+ people. The owner is a Trans woman.

name: Lebanon Public Library
directions: The side entrance (Bank Street) is accessible to wheelchair users. This entrance opens into the children's room (ground floor) which has a bathroom and a caregiver's room at the opposite end of the room from the entrance. Take the elevator or stairs down one floor (basement level) to access one of the library's other bathrooms, which is single user and has free pads and tampons. Take the elevator or stairs up to the first floor to access the other bathroom, which is also single user and has free pads and tampons.
comment: Doors to all of the bathrooms and the caregiver's room can be locked. The teen room on the second floor (elevator or stairs) has a set of drawers with free hygiene supplies (face wipes, lotion, toothbrushes, etc).

name: Kilton Public Library
comment: Two accessible, all gender bathrooms with multiple stalls each. The stall dividers go all the way to the floor for complete privacy. One bathroom has a baby changing table and one has an adult changing table. Each bathroom has a sharps disposal box. The bathroom with the baby changing table has free pads and tampons.

name: Infinitus Pie
